<div class="comment" id="comment-47780067">
  <div class="comment_head"><a href="/user/siliconc0w">siliconc0w</a> 2 minutes ago</div>
  <div class="comment_text">The problem with AI is that it isn&#x27;t like any previous technology.  There may be temporary jobs to fill in the gaps but they won&#x27;t be careers.  The AI will do the process engineering and self optimization.  The prompt witchcraft is a good example because today its totally unnecessary and doesn&#x27;t actually increase performance, and they&#x27;ll continue to make it easier to direct&#x2F;steer the models.<p>We&#x27;re literally trying to build an intelligence to replace us.</div>
  
